  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Emergency and Lifesaving Multisectoral Assistance in Response to Floods in Bentiu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to provide emergency assistance to flood-affected populations, with a focus on Unity, Jonglei and Lakes States through targeted CCCM, WASH, and S-NFI frontline and pipeline engagements. 

IOM CCCM has carried out site mitigation measures for  33,692 IDPs since the onset of the flooding, providing lifesaving support by securing IDP sites around Bentiu and Rubkona, to ensure that the main supply road is not submerged with water. Building on the already ongoing government-led response in Rubkona town, IOM are scaling up the site development activities by supporting the government to identify adequate land with proper site planning, plot demarcation and allocation for shelters and community facilities that are necessary for a dignified living condition and safe environment.

Through in-kind emergency shelter and non-food items (ES-NFI) support and cash assistance for the most vulnerable households, including women and child-headed families and persons with disabilities, IOM aim to meet the emergency ES-NFI needs of 65,766 flood-affected individuals in Unity and Jonglei through frontline activities and a total of 80,272 flood-affected individuals through the ES-NFI Pipeline. In addition, IOM engage the community in constructing and repairing the dike, extending support by providing sandbags, and hiring an excavator to protect residential areas from further flooding.



WASH engagements will ultimately reach 146,659 individuals for both frontline and pipeline activities. As the agency also managing part of the WASH Cluster Pipeline, IOM are procuring for replenishment critical WASH supplies that have been released for WASH partner agencies&#x2019; flood response and are still being requested for prioritized locations in the states of Jonglei, Unity, Upper Nile, Lakes, and Warrap. WASH frontline engagements in IDP camps are reaching IDPs and host communities in Bentiu and Rubkona town. They will focus on providing critical water, sanitation, and hygiene services that will assist these communities restoring access to basic life-saving services, to strengthen health outcomes and prevent WASH-related public health hazards linked to the flooding.</narrative>
  </description>
